      {
        "id": "presentation-guide",
        "title": "Presentation Guide",
        "scrollable": true,
        "root": [
          {
            "tag": "h1",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-4xl font-bold text-indigo-700 text-center"
            },
            "children": [{ "text": "Whales – Guardians of the Climate" }]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h1",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-4xl font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-6 text-center"
            },
            "children": [{ "text": "Lesson 8: Presentation" }]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h3",
            "attributes": { "class": "text-2xl font-bold text-blue-600" },
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "SAMPLE OUTLINE FOR PRESENTATION: “Whales – Guardians of the Climate”"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "p",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "This is a sample outline for your presentation about "
              },
              {
                "tag": "strong",
                "children": [{ "text": "Whales – Guardians of the Climate" }]
              },
              {
                "text": ". You can use it as a model or adapt it. The outline includes both the "
              },
              { "tag": "strong", "children": [{ "text": "onscreen content" }] },
              { "text": " (what appears on the slide) and the " },
              { "tag": "strong", "children": [{ "text": "speaker script" }] },
              { "text": " (what you say during your presentation)." }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h4",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 pt-2"
            },
            "children": [{ "text": "1. Understanding the Goal" }]
          },
          { "tag": "p", "children": [{ "text": "This presentation will:" }] },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Explain why whales are ‘engineers of the ocean’ and how they sustain life."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Summarize climate threats to oceans: warming, acidification, sea-level rise, stronger storms."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Describe how whales store carbon and fertilize phytoplankton that absorb CO2 and produce oxygen."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Highlight current threats to whales: ship strikes, fishing gear, and noise; include the North Atlantic right whale case."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "text": "Present actions to protect whales and climate: slower ships, safer fishing, protected habitats."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h4",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 pt-2"
            },
            "children": [
              { "text": "2. Presentation Structure (Slides Overview)" }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h5",
            "attributes": { "class": "text-lg font-semibold text-blue-600" },
            "children": [{ "text": "Slides 1–2: More Than Ocean Giants" }]
          },
          {
            "tag": "p",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Introduce whales as intelligent ocean engineers and why they matter for the planet."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " whales’ size, intelligence, and role in moving nutrients and sustaining ocean life."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Script example:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " “Whales are not only majestic and intelligent - they are ‘engineers of the ocean’ that help circulate nutrients, support tiny plants, and keep Earth’s systems in balance.”"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h5",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 mt-4"
            },
            "children": [{ "text": "Slides 3–4: Oceans Under Threat" }]
          },
          {
            "tag": "p",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Explain climate-driven changes harming oceans and communities."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " warming oceans, acidification, melting ice, rising seas, and stronger storms."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Script example:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " “Human activity is changing the climate. Oceans are warming and becoming more acidic, sea levels are rising, and storms intensify - threatening marine life and coastal communities.”"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h5",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-lg font-semibold text-blue-600 mt-4"
            },
            "children": [{ "text": "Slides 5–6: How Whales Help the Planet" }]
          },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " whales store carbon over long lifetimes; when they die and sink (‘whale falls’), that carbon is locked away for centuries."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " whale waste fertilizes phytoplankton - tiny plants that absorb CO2 and produce about half of our oxygen."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Script example:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " “By boosting phytoplankton and storing carbon, whales help remove hundreds of millions of tonnes of CO2 from the atmosphere each year.”"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h5",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-lg font-semibold text-blue-600 mt-4"
            },
            "children": [{ "text": "Slides 7–8: A Struggle for Survival" }]
          },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " threats: ship collisions, entanglement in fishing gear, and underwater noise."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " the North Atlantic right whale - fewer than 400 individuals remain; many die slowly from injuries or starvation."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Script example:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " “Despite their importance, many whales face deadly dangers today, pushing some species dangerously close to extinction.”"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h5",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-lg font-semibold text-blue-600 mt-4"
            },
            "children": [
              { "text": "Slides 9–10: Protecting the Ocean’s Giants" }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " preventing ship strikes (speed limits, routing), improving fishing practices (ropeless gear), and creating safer habitats."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Script example:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " “Saving whales means saving the planet. Each whale that survives helps keep oceans healthy and the atmosphere cleaner.”"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h5",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-lg font-semibold text-blue-600 mt-4"
            },
            "children": [
              { "text": "Slide 11: Why Protecting Whales Protects the Climate" }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " whales help oceans stay productive and boost oxygen through phytoplankton."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " carbon storage and long-term sequestration when whales sink."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      { "tag": "strong", "children": [{ "text": "Script:" }] },
                      {
                        "text": " “By protecting whales, we strengthen the systems that give us air to breathe and a stable climate to live in.”"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "h5",
            "attributes": {
              "class": "text-lg font-semibold text-blue-600 mt-4"
            },
            "children": [
              { "text": "Slides 12–13: Call to Action and Conclusion" }
            ]
          },
          {
            "tag": "ul",
            "attributes": { "class": "list-inside ml-6 space-y-1" },
            "children": [
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      {
                        "tag": "strong",
                        "children": [{ "text": "Talk about:" }]
                      },
                      {
                        "text": " what governments and individuals can do: reduce emissions, protect habitats, adopt safer shipping and fishing."
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "li",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "tag": "span",
                    "children": [
                      { "tag": "strong", "children": [{ "text": "Script:" }] },
                      {
                        "text": " “By protecting whales, we protect the ocean and the climate. Let’s act now so future generations inherit healthy seas and a livable planet.”"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "containerClassName": "bg-white bg-opacity-90 rounded-xl p-10 shadow-2xl text-xl"
      }
    ]
  }
